I"É<p>The Storage4Grid project has officially appointed another new member of the External Stakeholder Group (ESG). He is:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Enrique Troncoso (<a href="http://www.systengconsulting.com/">Systeng Consulting</a>)</li>
</ul>

<p>Enrique Troncoso has worked with energy storage technologies and their implementation on grid and microgrid applications for over 15 years, and has developed and led several R&amp;D and demonstration projects in this area, including techno-economic analyses and development of business cases for implementation of energy storage technologies into grid applications (e.g. provision of ancillary services).</p>

<p>ESG members will play a key role in keeping the Storage4Grid vision aligned with the strategies of storage providers and the opportunities raising from new developments in Energy Storage technologies and systems.</p>

<p>More information on the <a href="/pages/esg.html">External Stakeholders Group (ESG) page</a>.</p>
